    "filters": "Filters",
    "filterResult": "{{numFound}} object/s",
    "help": "<h1>Filter drawer</h1><p>By setting filters, the result set of the search can be further limited.</p><p>Using the thematically grouped <b>content filters</b>, it is possible to restrict the result set to manuscripts for which there are <b>scholarly descriptions, digital images</b> or –more precisely- <b>IIIF compliant digital images</b> that can be opened in the Workspace. The selection is linked with AND, so results must fulfil both conditions.</p><p>The <b>options</b> displayed for the various filters are taken from the current result set - i.e. only values are displayed that occur in at least one manuscript in the result set.</p><p>The <b>numbers</b> behind the individual filter options show the number of manuscripts that fulfil the respective condition. Selecting an option will immediately update these numbers as well as the total number of handwritings matching the current filtering, shown in the top right-hand corner.</p><p>By setting filters, the <b>statistical composition</b> of the hit list can already be examined before the filtering is applied to the hit list via the red button at the bottom of the drawer. The X at the top right can be used to discard changes made to the filtering.</p><p>Selections made in <b>different filters</b> (e.g. <i>Material</i> and <i>Place of origin</i>) are linked with AND, so matching results must fulfil both conditions.</br><b>Different options</b> selected in one filter (e.g. <i>Parchment</i> and <i>Paper</i>) are linked with OR, so results are shown for both parchment and paper manuscripts.</p><p>Most filters also offer the option <i>\"(Empty)\"</i> in addition to the values occurring in the result set. If this option is selected, results are taken into account for which the corresponding <b>value is not occupied</b> (e.g. manuscripts without a stated place of origin).</p><p>When filtering according to the <b>Date of origin</b>, a period of time can be specified within which the manuscript is supposed to have been created. Since for some manuscripts only periods for their date of origin are known, there is a slider <i>\"Period completely within range\"</i>. It can be used to select whether manuscripts should be displayed where the period of origin only overlaps with the specified period or whether the period of origin known for the manuscript has to lie completely within the specified range.</p>",
    "helpLabel": "Help",
